Zuma was speaking outside the Pietermaritzburg High Court after the outcome of his application for permanent stay of prosecution was reserved. He says when the State Capture commission was announced and got underway many had thought that Zuma will be implicated but he claims this has not materialised. Zuma maintains he is innocent. Zuma who is charged along with the French arms company Thales face 16 counts of corruption, fraud and racketeering.
--SABC--